projects.name: Bitcoin Hyper
projects.desc: A Layer-2 solution for Bitcoin focused on scalability, aiming to attract both Bitcoin maximalists and DeFi developers. It promises significant transaction throughput improvements and is positioned for explosive growth, with projected 50–100× returns for early investors.

projects.name: Remittix
projects.desc: A blockchain-based remittance platform targeting the $750B global remittance market. Remittix leverages deflationary tokenomics to enable low-cost, cross-border payments, aiming to disrupt traditional money transfer services and deliver 20–50× returns for early adopters.

projects.name: Ozak AI
projects.desc: A tech-focused project combining artificial intelligence and blockchain, utilizing Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) networks for enterprise scalability. Ozak AI is positioned for mass adoption in 2026 and has secured over $375M in funding, indicating strong institutional interest.

projects.name: BlockDAG
projects.desc: An enterprise-grade blockchain project leveraging DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) architecture for high scalability and throughput. BlockDAG aims to solve bottlenecks in traditional blockchains and is targeting mass adoption with significant funding and technical innovation.

projects.name: Internet Computer
projects.desc: A decentralized computing platform enabling direct hosting of web applications and services on a public blockchain. Recent upgrades (Tokamak, Beryllium, Stellarator) have improved performance and scalability. ICP is integrating AI and expanding interoperability, including with Solana, to solidify its role in decentralized infrastructure.

projects.name: Toncoin
projects.desc: The native token of The Open Network, originally developed by Telegram and now run by an independent community. TON stands out for its scalability and potential integration with Telegram’s massive user base, making it a promising candidate for mainstream adoption.
